ce:section.ce:para:
The microwave might have a synergistic effect or influence with other factors in the process of hydrothermal reaction to prepare CDs. Therefore, the effect of microwave on S-CDs luminescence characteristics at different reaction temperatures (Fig. 7
                        ) and residence time (Fig. 8
                        ) was further investigated. As shown in Figs. 7 and 8, under the same test conditions and using an excitation wavelength of 400 nm, the intensities of the fluorescence emission spectra of SMHTC-CDs were all stronger than that of SHTC-CDs among the several working conditions investigated in this paper. This result could be explained from two aspects: first, the non-thermal action of microwave coupled with the reactants during the generation of S-CDs, promoting the reaction of cracking, cross-linking, agglomeration, condensation and carbonization, and thus more carbon nano-particles were generated, and the macroscopic luminescence intensity of S-CDs was enhanced; Second, as the above analysis, microwave non-thermal action had a positive effect on the chemical structure and functional properties of S-CDs, so that more surface states and intrinsic states that were conducive to reducing band gaps and enhancing luminescence were formed, and thus microscopic luminescence was enhanced. The above work revealed the differences in the structure and properties of S-CDs caused by microwave non-thermal effect and provided a new approach for the regulation of CDs performance.
